Use the standard library
This is how to minPath of grid and k:
   Remember that rows is grid's length
   Remember that prev is []
   Remember that j is 0
   Do this rows times:
      Add prev to item 0 in item j in grid
      Increase j
   End do

   Remember that step is 1
   Do this k times:
      When step is more than k, then:
         Leave the loop
      End when

      Remember that curr is []
      Remember that i is 0
      Do this rows times:
         Remember that best is item i in prev

         When i is more than 0, then:
            Remember that up is item (diff of i and 1) in prev
            When up is less than best, then:
               Remember that best is up
            End when
         End when

         When i is less than (diff of rows and 1), then:
            Remember that down is item (sum of i and 1) in prev
            When down is less than best, then:
               Remember that best is down
            End when
         End when

         Remember that val is sum of best and item step in item i in grid
         Add curr to val
         Increase i
      End do

      Remember that prev is curr
      Increase step
   End do

   The answer is prev
Now you know